{"word":"H5102 - נָהַר - nâhar - naw-har' - Flow","slug":"H5102","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נָהַר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nâhar"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>naw-har'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Flow"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05D4;&#x05E8; - na&#x0302;har</b> - <i>naw-har'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>sparkle</i>, that is, (figuratively) <i>be cheerful</i>; hence (from the <i>sheen</i> of a running stream) to <i>flow</i>, that is, (figuratively) <i>assemble: - </i>flow (together), be lightened."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4492\">H4492</a>, <a href=\"#/H5105\">H5105</a>"}]}